      <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">
          Putin’s Victory Day 
       </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
        <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
         <strong>Summary: Putin's big expectations for this year’s Victory Day parade face obstacles.</strong>
         </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Vladimir Putin hopes the May 9 Victory Day parade will restore Russia's global relevance. Twenty-nine world leaders are on the guest list, with many planning to attend. This number is the highest since Russia's war with Ukraine in 2022. However, some of these hopes are fading due to recent issues. 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Illnesses might prevent Presidents Fico of Slovakia and Vucic of Serbia from attending. Even if they attend, the Baltic states intend to <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-8-may-25-analysis-h1-6-close-their-airspace" target="_blank">close their airspace</a> to any plane carrying them. EU warnings and Ukrainian drone strikes on Moscow are raising security concerns.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Zelenskyy stated he <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-8-may-25-analysis-h1-7-could-not-assure" target="_blank">could not assure</a> the safety of attendees, complicating the event further. Meanwhile, the United States has shown more recent support for Ukraine by signing a critical minerals agreement, signaling long-term backing. Russia’s grand military display will include North Korean troops for the first time, while Ukraine will observe May 8 with quiet remembrance and European-style ceremonies, which are more solemn affairs.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
         Victory Day has become a battleground for narratives. Russia frames its conflicts as a continuation of its WWII legacy. Ukraine and the Baltic states reject this view. Russia has repeatedly used this war as a way to intervene in Ukraine as it uses the narrative that it is fighting nazis and facism like it did in the second world war.</p>
        </mj-text>
