      <mj-spacer height="10px"/>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           <strong>🇭🇺 Hungary - EU commission sues.</strong> The European Commission is suing Hungary for violating EU law after it released over 2,000 convicted migrant smugglers, requiring only that they leave the country. Critics say the move undermines EU anti-smuggling efforts. Many released offenders entered other Schengen countries, prompting diplomatic tensions and increased border controls, especially from Austria (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-8-may-25-worldwide-8-hungary-does-it-again" target="_blank">Hungary does it again</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           <strong>🇨🇦 Canada - Alberta separatism.</strong> Alberta Premier Danielle Smith says she will honor a citizen-led referendum on provincial separation in 2026 if enough signatures are gathered, though she personally opposes separation. Indigenous leaders strongly condemned the move, arguing it violates treaties and warning of legal actions (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-8-may-25-worldwide-9-referendum-games" target="_blank">referendum games</a>). 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           <strong>🇮🇳 India - Agreement with the UK.</strong> The UK and India signed a landmark free trade deal cutting tariffs on British whisky, cars, and other goods, while India gains duty-free access for 99% of its exports. The agreement is expected to boost annual trade by $34B by 2040 (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-8-may-25-worldwide-10-finerprint" target="_blank">fine print</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           <strong>🇫🇷 France - Joint security efforts.</strong> French President Emmanuel Macron and newly elected German Chancellor Friedrich Merz pledged to strengthen defense cooperation by creating a joint security council. Merz also proposed talks with France and Britain on European nuclear deterrence (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-8-may-25-worldwide-11-franco-german-relations" target="_blank">Franco-German relations</a>). 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           <strong>🇪🇬 Egypt - Challenging marine agreements.</strong> 
           Dozens of Egyptian lawyers appealed a 2016 deal transferring Red Sea islands Tiran and Sanafir to Saudi Arabia, claiming it violates Egypt’s constitution. Public backlash resurged amid reports Saudi Arabia invited the US to build a base there (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-8-may-25-worldwide-12-boundary-issues" target="_blank">boundary issues</a>).
          </p>
          
        </mj-text>
