          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">
         What is Victory in Europe Day?
</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/victory-in-europe-day-may-8-german-surrender.png" alt="The eighth of May marked the day when German troops throughout Europe finally laid down their arms" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;">
          <i>The eighth of May marked the day when German troops throughout Europe finally laid down their arms. Credits: Bettmann Archive/Getty Images</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">     
        Victory in Europe (VE) Day is celebrated on May 8 every year. It marks <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-8-may-25-foundations-h1-13-the-formal-surrender" target="_blank">the formal surrender</a> of Nazi Germany to the Allied forces in 1945. This event effectively ended the Second World War in Europe. On May 7, 1945, Nazi Germany signed an unconditional surrender. The next day was declared VE Day. However, the war did not end in the Pacific until August 1945.
        </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        Different European countries observe it in unique ways. While it is celebrated to mark the end of Nazi germany's take over on Europe, it is also a day of reflection on the impact of the war and the rebuilding of Europe in the post-war era. In some countries, it is observed with military parades, ceremonies, and moments of silence.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        While most historians say a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-8-may-25-foundations-h1-14-joint-effort-clinched" target="_blank">joint effort clinched</a> the war, some critics say Western countries emphasized the US or Britain clinching the war when the Soviets did most of the heavy lifting and triumphed in more crucial battles. The debate goes back and forth on how much the US and other allied powers contributed.</p>
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        Moreover, it is also a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-8-may-25-foundations-h1-15-sensitive-subject" target="_blank">sensitive subject</a> in some Eastern European countries, where people feel conflicted about the day. However, the Russians constructed propaganda around the victory, claiming they had liberalized the region.</p>
        </mj-text>
